    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-18T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="515"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1189: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-18T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 18, 1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 18—8:25
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. To Council Committee’s telegram (Wilson’s 115, February 16, 8 p.m.) Peru
                    replied under date of February 16 complaining of Colombian aggression in
                    attacking Peruvian posts at Tarapacá.</p>
                <p>To this the Committee replied on February 17 in substance as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Since Tarapacá is on Colombian territory can hardly understand how
                            Peruvian military posts are there and would appreciate earliest
                            information on point.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>At urgent request of Colombia, Council meeting is contemplated for Monday.</p>
                <p>It is understood that Colombia is invoking article 15.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
